1 prescription drug monitoring to carry out the purposes of section
2 71-2454. The department may use state funds and accept grants, gifts, or
3 other funds in order to implement and operate the technology. The
4 department may adopt and promulgate rules and regulations to authorize
5 use of electronic health information, if necessary to carry out the
6 purposes of sections 71-2454 and 71-2455. The department shall contract
7 with a vendor pursuant to the State Procurement Act the statewide health
8 information exchange for the administration of the Health Information
9 Technology Board, and such contract shall specify that the vendor health
10 information exchange is responsible for the administration of the Health
11 Information Technology Board, including, but not limited to, providing
12 meeting notices, recording and distributing meeting minutes,
13 administrative tasks related to the same, and funding such activities.
14 The contract shall also include provisions for the vendor statewide
15 health information exchange to reimburse the expenses of the members of
16 the board pursuant to subsection (5) of section 81-6,127. Such
17 reimbursement shall be paid using a process essentially similar to
18 sections 81-1174 to 81-1177. No state funds, including General Funds,
19 cash funds, and federal funds, shall be used to carry out the
20 administrative duties of the Health Information Technology Board nor for
21 reimbursement of the expenses of the board members.
